===Etymology===
From the concept of [[martyrdom]] through [[fire]].

===Alternate forms===
* baptism of fire

===Noun phrase=== 
'''baptism by fire''' (''Plural:'' '''baptisms by fire''')

# A rite of passage through the survival or sucess of a [[crisis]].
# A trying [[ordeal]] that was not experienced before.
# A change in initial attitude or ideals through a [[traumatic]] situation.

